===Verb===
{{en-verb}} {{term-label|en|commonly|_|US}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To familiarize with a situation or circumstance.
#: {{synonyms|en|orientate|q1=commonly Britain}}
#: {{ux|en|Give him time to '''orient''' himself within the new hierarchy.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[point]] at or [[direct]] towards.
#: {{ux|en|I will '''orient''' all of the signs to face the road.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[determine]] which direction one is facing.
#: {{ux|en|Let me just '''orient''' myself and we can be on our way.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[place]] or [[build]] so as to [[face]] [[eastward]].
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To place (a map or chart) so that its east side, north side, etc., lie toward the corresponding parts of the horizon; {{lb|en|specifically|surveying}} to rotate (a map attached to a plane table) until the line of direction between any two of its points is parallel to the corresponding direction in nature.
